item.title: I fucked up my emote tele list help!
item.dc:creator: @sp3c sp3c
item.description:
@sp3c wrote:

Nope that’s not where u are needing to put it. Search in client.java for: case 164: You should have a case 164 already. Just replace the case 164 and whats under it until u get to the other case, and then show me what u have.

EDIT: do this:

Replace:

case 164: // bow emote startAnimation(0x35A); break;

With:

case 164:// a tele emote teleportToX = LOCATION X; teleportToY = LOCATION Y; inwildy = false; sendMessage("YOUR MESSAGE HERE");

After that ctr+f and then type in //first emote slot.
It should look a lil something like this, but not exact:

sendFrame126("@whi@Bank", 180);//first emote slot

Replace with:

sendFrame126("@whi@"WHAT U WANT THE EMOTE TO SAY ON EMOTES LIST", 180);//first emote slot

item.title: I fucked up my emote tele list help!
item.dc:creator: @sp3c sp3c
item.description:
@sp3c wrote:

Simple to add emotes for teles. First find case 169. That starts the emote list. I will use case 164 for this.

case 164://jad teleportToX = 3098; teleportToY = 3934; inwildy = false; sendMessage("GOOD LUCK KILLING JAD!");

The case is a case for the emotes list. Forgot which slot. But teleporttox = 3098; is the x axis.
teleportoy = 3934 is the y axis. just ignore the inwildy = false; but leave it there. And the send message just sends them a message when they get there. This is for a jad teleport in my server.

Also to make it show up on the emotes list find:

//first emote slot

And then, depending which slot u want it in, just put “jad” in there.

example of mine:

sendFrame126("@red@Jad",175);//fourth emote slot

There u go, that should do it, just edit the cords to where u want, the message to what it says.
